# TypeScript Rules

## Domain Types — Single Source of Truth

All shared domain types live in `zafora-frontend/src/lib/types/domain.ts`:

```ts
Lead · Project · ProjectInterest · Document · CatalogService
Testimonial · ContentStat · MethodologyStep · SiteSetting
AuditLog · DashboardStats · ProjectStats
```

Import them as: `import type { Lead, Project } from "@/src/lib/types";`

Do NOT redefine these inline in components.

## No `any`

```ts
// ❌ BAD
const data: any = res.data;

// ✅ GOOD
const data: Lead[] = res.data.leads;
// or if truly unknown:
const data: unknown = res.data;
const leads = data as { leads: Lead[] };
```

## Zod Validators

- Live in `zafora-frontend/src/lib/validators/` — hand-written, no Orval/codegen
- Infer types: `type CreateLeadInput = z.infer<typeof CreateLeadBody>`
- Backend: `zafora-backend/src/modules/*/[module].validator.ts`
- Use `zod/v4` in backend (`import { z } from "zod/v4"`)

## Path Alias

```ts
// ✅ Always
import { apiAxios } from "@/src/lib/api-helpers";
import { ROUTES } from "@/src/lib/url-helpers";

// ❌ Never relative for cross-module imports
import { apiAxios } from "../../../../../../lib/api-helpers";
```

## Backend Type Pattern

```ts
// Infer from Drizzle schema — never duplicate
export type Lead = typeof leadsTable.$inferSelect;
export type InsertLead = z.infer<typeof insertLeadSchema>;
```

## Module-Local Types

Keep params/response types inline in the service file unless 2+ modules need them:
```ts
// leads.service.ts — local, not exported to lib/types
type ListLeadsParams = { status?: string; page?: number; limit?: number };
```
